# Release artifacts go here.
#
# Binaries are NOT committed to git. They are built locally with
#   npm run release:windows
# (or :macos / :linux when those scripts exist) and uploaded to a
# distribution channel — currently GitHub Releases.
#
# What lives here:
#   *.exe           NSIS installer (smaller, friendlier)
#   *.msi           Windows Installer package (IT-managed deploys)
#   *.dmg           macOS disk image
#   *.deb / *.rpm   Linux native packages
#   *.AppImage      Linux portable
#   SHA256SUMS.txt  checksums for the above (committed-friendly text)
#   RELEASE_NOTES.md per-version changelog excerpt
#
# Anything binary is gitignored via /releases/.gitignore — the README
# stays so the directory is always present in the tree.

# Ignore every binary artifact.
*.exe
*.msi
*.dmg
*.deb
*.rpm
*.AppImage
*.sig
*.zip
*.tar.gz

# But keep the human-facing files.
!README.md
!.gitignore
!SHA256SUMS.txt
!RELEASE_NOTES*.md
